•Qualifications Requires Bachelor’s degree (in Computer Science or related field) or equivalent, and seven to nine years of related experience.
•Serve as a JIRA administrator and engineer with DevOps experience.
•Will be responsible for administration, maintenance, upgrades, and enhancements to JIRA, Fisheye, Bamboo, Crowd and integration with other tools or plugins.
•Administer JIRA software and formulate technical solutions using JIRA and associated JIRA plugins or    
   Atlassian products.
•Create JIRA projects, queries, and reports, as needed.
•Create custom workflows, post functions, and validators, make changes to workflows, screens, fields, and reporting, and provide ongoing support and configuration maintenance.
•Develop solutions extending Atlassian REST services and JIRA plugins using the Atlassian SDK.
•Experience with build, automation, and artifact technologies: Ant, Gradle, Maven, Jenkins, Artifactory
•Experience with SVN required and good to have experience in git
•Experience in Linux Administration (RHEL, CentOS)
•Experience with Shell and Python scripting
•Experience with Atlassian suite of products (Jira, Confluence, Bitbucket)
•Experience with containers and build pipelines tools: Docker, Jenkins Pipelines
•Familiarity with cloud computing concepts.
•Knowledge/Experience on Tomcat and SQL
•Knowledge/Experience on various OS.
•Knowledge/Exposure to Continuous Integration.
